2	 * Deal calculation logic for the in-app settlement tool.
3	 *
4	 * IMPORTANT — DELIBERATELY INCOMPLETE.
5	 *
6	 * This is the existing Greenroom settlement engine. It was built early in
7	 * the company's life, when most deals were flat guarantees. It currently
8	 * handles two deal types end-to-end:
9	 *
10	 *   1. flat                 — $X guaranteed, optional sellout bonus
11	 *   2. percentage_of_gross  — X% of gross, no expense deductions, optional sellout bonus
12	 *
13	 * For both, it reads `bonusesJson` and applies bonuses where it can — but
14	 * only the structured ones. Bonuses that exist only in `dealNotesFreetext`
15	 * are invisible to this engine.
16	 *
17	 * It does NOT handle:
18	 *
19	 *   - vs deals (guarantee vs % of net, whichever greater)
20	 *   - percentage_of_net deals (with expense deductions)
21	 *   - door deals
22	 *   - recoups (those flow separately through the settlement record)
23	 *   - tier ratchets (would need vs-deal support first)
24	 *   - comps that count toward gross
25	 *
26	 * For unsupported deals, the tool returns { supported: false } and the UI
27	 * shows the "this deal type isn't yet supported" empty state. About 82% of
28	 * Greenroom's customers default to spreadsheets because of this.
29	 */
30	
